## User Auth (from the frontend)

### Sign up
```bash
curl -s -X POST "$SUPABEIN_URL/api/v1/auth/signup" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"user@example.com","password":"secret123"}'
# returns { token: "eyJ..." }
```

### Log in
```bash
curl -s -X POST "$SUPABEIN_URL/api/v1/auth/login" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"email":"user@example.com","password":"secret123"}'
# returns { token: "eyJ..." }
```

Use the returned JWT as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` for authenticated data API calls.

